headline: Eversource Earnings Beat And US$26.5b Plan Reshape Utility Outlook
summary: Eversource Energy (NYSE:ES) released fourth quarter and full year 2025 results that came in ahead of analyst expectations. The company outlined a long term investment plan of $26.5b for 2026 to 2030, focused on energy infrastructure, affordability and system upgrades. Management also updated longer term guidance to reflect the new spending plan and priorities around reliability and customer costs.
